description:
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Join our staff bank and be a valued member of the team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Bank Band 7 Senior MRI Radiographer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span&gt; We are recruiting for highly motivated and talented Senior MRI Radiographer for a line of work based in St Mary’s Hospital for Imperial Staff Bank. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;A suitable worker must be flexible to work any of the shift patterns 5 days a week across Monday- Saturday. Possible shifts are; 07.45-16.15, 09.45-18.15, 09.45-18.15, 12.00-20.00 or 14.00-22.00; please note the service only runs one shift on a Saturday this would be 09.00 – 17.15. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is a Senior band 7 role therefore suitable workers may supervise and line manage band 6 staff and students, they may also be required to manage the service alone for part of a shift. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Rate of Pay: &lt;strong&gt;£25.86&lt;/strong&gt; (including WTR, pay rate depending on day and time worked)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Your Experience: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Minimum of 2 years MRI skills within CNS, MSK, Thorax (Breast, Cardiac), Abdomen, Pelvis, Vascular and Trauma.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previously worked with Paediatrics and Adults as well as sedated, intubated and non-intubated.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Must hold SOR/ University accredited IV certificate of competency&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Must have acute hospital experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Previous experience using GE systems&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Working Bank shifts is easy:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We value all of our staff and aim to provide rewarding careers and benefits, fulfilling work environments and exciting opportunities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Benefits for you:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Great Opportunity to progress within the Imperial College Healthcare NHS Trust&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Weekly Payments&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Competitive Pay Rates&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Platform to gain experience in different areas&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Friendly team environment&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Efficient Recruitment Process&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Complimentary Mandatory Training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Location: St Mary’s Hospital (MRI units)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Special skills: Advanced Radiographer who holds minimum of 2 years MRI skills within CNS, MSK, Thorax (Breast, Cardiac), Abdomen, Pelvis, Vascular and Trauma. Previously worked with Paediatrics and Adults as well as sedated, intubated and non-intubated&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must hold SOR/ university accredited IV certificate of competence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiar with working in an acute hospital setting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;MR scanners to work on&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Suitable workers must a minimum of 1 years GE systems experience. The following systems are used in this role:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1.5T GE HDX MR systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3T GE VR750 MR systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Shift patterns: Suitable workers must be flexible to work any shift 5 days a weeks between Monday – Saturday&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Potential shifts: 07:45-16:15 , 09:00-17:30, 09:45-18:15, 12:00-20:00, 14:00-22:00. The service runs one shift on a Saturday 09.00 – 17.15.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Contact a friendly member of our recruitment team on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;0203 312 7881 or imperial.staffbank.recruitment@nhs.net&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;IMPORTANT:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Please ensure you check your emails regularly as this is how we will communicate with you throughout the recruitment process. &lt;em&gt;Please note that due to a high volume of applications, if you have not been contacted in two weeks your application has been unsuccessful.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
